topic.title: Client Mapping Datapath Segment Provisioning API Details

body.p: The flowchart for provisioning client mapping into OTN is shown in Figure 1 below and uses the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API.

note.p: The source file for the following diagram can be found at http://bby1dms01.pmc-sierra.internal/DocMgmt/getfile.cfm?file_id=444764 (sheet "Client_MAP")

section.title: g5_api_client_map_cfg()
section.p: The g5_api_client_map_cfg() API provisions MAPOTN segment, CoreOTN FO2 as well as any other segments and mapping connections to ECPB and DCPB data paths based on the provided mode and channel ID. The API parameters are shown below with any associated enumerated types.

The device_id parameter is the device instance. For transparent Ethernet segment provisioning, the matching Ethernet channel from the g5_api_enet_prov() API is used for the chnl_id. For terminated Ethernet segment provisioning, the matching Ethernet channel from the g5_api_enet_prov() API is used for the chnl_id of g5_api_client_map_cfg() API.
The client mapping mode is specified by the parameter mode of the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API uses the g5_client_adaptation_mode_t enumeration.
Transparent Ethernet mapping modes of g5_client_adaptation_mode_t are shown in Table 1 below.

section.p: The parameter client_num_incr of the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API specifies the number of 1.25G tributary slots required to transport the GFP client in ODUflex(GFP) or 25G bit rate increments required to transport the FlexE client in ODUflex.
The parameter gfp_slice of the g5_api_client_map_cfg() API specifies the explicit GFP slice assignment or automatic slice assignment. This is used for GFP modes only.
